
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Student {
    +String studentID
    +String name
    +List<Course> registeredCourses
}

class TeachingAssistant {
    +String taID
    +String name
    +List<Course> assignedCourses
}

class Course {
    +String courseCode
    +String title
}

class Appointment {
    +DateTime appointmentTime
    +String topic
    +Course relatedCourse
}

' Relationships between classes

Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registers for
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Course : is TA for

Student "1" -- "1" Appointment : requests
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "1" Appointment : provides help for

Appointment "1" -- "1" Course : is for

' Constraints
note right of Appointment
  An appointment must be for a single course.
  A student can only request an appointment 
  if they are registered for that course.
  A TA can only provide appointments for courses they are assigned to.
end note

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **Student**: Has an ID, name, and list of registered courses. Can make appointments only for courses they're registered in.
- **TeachingAssistant**: Has an ID, name, and list of courses they are TAs for. Can only create appointments for these courses.
- **Course**: Identified by code and title. Serves as a bridge between students and TAs.
- **Appointment**: Links a student, a teaching assistant, and a specific course. It contains time and topic.

